parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the HDM can cause the headlights to malfunction or fail, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: The headlights do not turn on
the low-beam headlights fail to operate
the headlights become inoperable without warning
the headlights shut off suddenly
the headlights fail to illuminate
the high beams are activated to compensate for failed low beams.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
warning lights illuminate on the instrument panel
the engine loses power
the starter delays
the key fails to remain in the run position
the ignition switch fails
and the fuse box catches fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The key fails to remain in the run position
the ignition switch fails
the vehicle stalls or loses power
and the warning lights illuminate on the instrument panel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlights can cause reduced visibility, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The headlights fail to illuminate
the low beams suddenly go out
and the daytime lights fail to operate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuse box can cause a fire, leading to injuries or property damage.
symptoms: The fuse box catches fire
the wiring harness under the hood catches fire
and the headlight control in the fuse panel overheats and begins to burn a hole in the fuse panel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn, making it hard to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: Grinding or clicking noise when turning the steering wheel
loose or rattling steering column
clunking sound when turning
stiff steering
and power steering fluid leaks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn, making it hard to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: Loss of power steering
stiff steering
grinding or whining noise when turning
power steering fluid leaks
and difficulty turning the steering wheel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the stabilizer bar can cause the vehicle to lose control, making it difficult to steer, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: Cracking or breaking of the stabilizer bar
clunking or grinding noise when turning
and loss of vehicle control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the tie rod can cause the vehicle to lose control, making it difficult to steer, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: Clunking or grinding noise when turning
loose or worn-out tie rod ends
and difficulty steering the vehicle.
